17 2021-03-03 chest discomfort Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes ... Read more
Close
Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes to 1 hour after receiving her second Moderna vaccination on 2/24/21. She reported that she was told by her employer that the symptoms were due to the Moderna vaccine. She reportedly developed fever and some throat discomfort as well. Symptoms became persistent and disrupted sleep and was unable to work. She sought medical attention in the ER for persistent symptoms on 2/26/21. Extensive workup was essentially normal. She received Zofran, Decadron, IVFs, and Albuterol inhaler while in the ER. She reported improvement in her chest tightness and SOB after Albuterol. She was discharged home with instructions to f/u with her PCP in a couple of days for recheck.
17 2021-04-17 fainting Vasovagal Syncope; unauthorized age patient, 17 years of age; This spontaneous case was reported by ... Read more
Close
Vasovagal Syncope; unauthorized age patient, 17 years of age; This spontaneous case was reported by a nurse and describes the occurrence of SYNCOPE (Vasovagal Syncope) in a 17-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 012A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. Concurrent medical conditions included Congenital heart disease NOS since 22-May-2003. On 01-Mar-2021 at 2:30 PM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 01-Mar-2021 at 2:30 PM, the patient experienced SYNCOPE (Vasovagal Syncope) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (unauthorized age patient, 17 years of age). On 01-Mar-2021, SYNCOPE (Vasovagal Syncope) had resolved. On 01-Mar-2021 at 2:30 PM, PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (unauthorized age patient, 17 years of age) had resolved. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter considered SYNCOPE (Vasovagal Syncope) to be unlikely related. No further causality assessment was provided for PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (unauthorized age patient, 17 years of age). No relevant concomitant medications were reported. The patient did not receive any treatment. The event, SYNCOPE (vasovagal syncope) was an acute episode and recovered quickly within minutes. Follow-up received on 06-APR-2021 included additional reporter information, date of vaccine administration, patient's race, ethnicity and other relevant medical history, start and dates of product administered and the events, anatomical location, and reporter causality. This report refers to a case of inappropriate schedule of vaccine administered for mRNA-1273 (lot #unknown) with no associated syncope reported. The reporter considered SYNCOPE to be unlikely related. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Most recent FOLLOW-UP information incorporated above includes: On 06-Apr-2021: additional reporter information, date of vaccine administration, patient's race, ethnicity and concurrent condition, additional event - Syncope, onset and stop dates of the event, - Product administered to patient of inappropriate age, injection site, and reporter causality.; Sender's Comments: This report refers to a case of inappropriate schedule of vaccine administered for mRNA-1273 (lot #unknown) with no associated syncope reported.The reporter considered SYNCOPE to be unlikely related. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

I feel like something is crawling under my skin and the vaccine is extremely affecting my nervous system. I did not have this problem before I had the vaccine. It has not gone away and it is now April 23rd I still feel weak, not the same as I used to feel before having the vaccine, and my muscles are twitching all over my body. My face is twitching and my eye and there is nothing I can do to make it stop. I am so young and I thought the vaccine was safe but I am suffering from it. Especially in my feet I feel like they are tingling and vibrating and my calves are convulsing too. Meanwhile, my heart is fluttering and I feel like it is very hard for me to focus and I feel things crawling under my skin in my brain. The muscle convulsions are happening everywhere.

18 2021-01-14 chest discomfort I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or ... Read more
Close
I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or an hour after. About 2 hours later (at 2:00 pm), I developed some hives around my neck, and the part of my arm near the injection site started to become more and more sore. I applied Benadryl to the hives and they went away. However, my left arm hurt to touch or move, much worse than any vaccine I've had before (flu, HPV). That night, I had trouble sleeping because the discomfort because of the sore left arm. I also could not sleep because of chest tightness and pressure, which worsened when lying down, but that pressure did not progress to the point of wheezing (I have asthma). Sleeping on my back was the only option because sleeping on either side was painful, which worsened the chest pressure. When I woke up, my fingers felt stiff and I had joint pain in both hands, more so in my left hand. Throughout this, I did not see any redness on my arm. This day it was agonizing to move my left arm. I could pick things up, but raising it above my the height of my waist or twisting it behind my back to get on my backpack was near impossible and was avoided. The chest pressure went away. The second night, I still had trouble sleeping, but the pain was much better, although I still could not sleep on my side. When I woke up, I had no more joint pain. That day, although the left arm was still sore, I could move it pretty well. If I made too strong of a movement, it felt like the injection site would tense up, the pain would slowly ramp up, and then diminish. That afternoon, at 4:30, I was able to play tennis with minimal soreness, and that night, I was able to sleep on my side. The following day, I had a cough, but that might have been because I didn't dress for the weather, and experiences close to zero soreness.

Woke up Thursday and still felt achy but functional with a headache and nausea. Same symptoms minus the nausea on Friday.

18 2021-02-17 blood pressure increased Patient received vaccine around 430pm. As she was sitting for post-vaccine observation she told an a... Read more
Close
Patient received vaccine around 430pm. As she was sitting for post-vaccine observation she told an associate to call over Rph due to side effects. After speaking with patient she stated that her arm was numb (vaccinated arm) and that it hurt more than when she got her flu shot. I assessed both arms an her vaccinated arm was slightly swollen. I described the signs of anaphylaxis to her and told her that i would like for her to stay longer for extra monitoring and to alarm me or one of my associates if any anaphylaxis symptoms occur. Patients blood pressure was taken reading - 132/96. Patient was unsure of her baseline so i explained i will check again shortly. Patient was given water and one dose of Benadryl (25mg) at 5:25pm as well as an ice pack to place on her arm. At 6:00pm patients blood pressure was retaken (124/82) and patient stated she was well enough to go home. Her grandma was with her and stated she didn't have Benadryl at home, I recommend her to get some and gave the patient another dose (25mg) before her grandma took her home. Patient has no primary care physician.

18 2021-03-10 increased heart rate, fast heart rate, chest discomfort 18 year old female came to hospital for chest tightness, choking sensation in the throat as well as ... Read more
Close
18 year old female came to hospital for chest tightness, choking sensation in the throat as well as skin rash after receiving COVID-19 vaccine. Initially patient presented to emergency room but subsequently discharged on steroid and Benadryl. Patient had continued episode of choking as well as chest tightness and skin rash for that patient came back to emergency room. Patient had received total 5 doses of epi pen because of that. Patient was admitted to medical floor initially. Patient was given steroid, Benadryl and famotidine. Patient had 2 episodes on medical floor where she started feeling choking and chest tightness. Patient remained stable hemodynamically except for tachycardia. Patient was transferred to intensive care unit for close monitoring. D-dimer was negative, urine tox screen was negative, COVID-19 PCR was negative, EKG showed sinus tachycardia. CT scan of neck was negative. We had discussed that patient has remained stable hemodynamically in the intensive care unit and discharge planning was discussed and patient was getting ready to be discharged when she had another episode where after drinking soda patient started having that choking sensation, patient remained stable hemodynamically during this episode as well. Her symptoms had improved. She looked visibly anxious. Patient was monitored in the ICU for few more hours and patient remained stable. I checked back on her and she was able to eat her lunch. She probably had a allergic reaction to more than a vaccine but subsequent episodes are thought to be secondary to anxiety attack given situation.

Close
Pt received vaccination at 1:30pm, pt ambulated to observation area, began feeling "dizzy and nauseous" while standing in observation area. Pt stated she continued to feel dizzy, and had tingling in her fingers. Vital signs reassessed at 1:43, BP 128/78, HR 80, unable to asses sp02 due to monitor not giving a reading. Vitals reassessed at 1:46pm, sp02 100%, HR 94. , began titrating oxygen supply down by 2l/min. Pt seemed to tolerate well for a few minutes, At 2:00pm, pt complained of tingling returning to her fingers, pt was receiving o2 4l/min, sp02 noted at 80%, increased 02 to 10l/min, called nursing lead who called 911. 2:10, unable to obtain accurate sp02. 2:17pm pt continues to receive 02 10l/min, stated she "feels okay, just weird and foggy" no tingling in hands. 2:20pm, paramedics arrive, pt states she is "a little bit dizzy" 2:35pm pt taken to hospital via stretcher with paramedics. Pt en route to hospital. At 2:00pm sp02 80%

18 2021-03-16 palpitations Approximately 7-8 minutes after receiving the vaccine, started to feel light-headed, thought she was... Read more
Close
Approximately 7-8 minutes after receiving the vaccine, started to feel light-headed, thought she was going to pass out, and her heart was racing extremely high. The health care team at the site took her blood pressure, measured heart rate, gave her water, juice and chocolate and tried to get her heart rate to drop. It was fluctuating up and down and she couldn't stand up without dizziness; we waited 45 minutes and then drove her home as she was unable to drive her own car. She was experiencing significant lightheadedness, and consistent heart racing even while lying down on the sofa/bed. This continued for several days and she stayed home from school and sports. We called her primary care doctor on the 10th and they suggested she wait another day to see how she was feeling. She started to feel a bit better by Friday, was still experiencing a bit of the tiredness, nauseous, light-headed and heart spikes, but was able to drive, move around. On Sunday evening, she started to experience increased heart rate again, lymph nodes were very painful and started experiencing the light headedness all evening. On Monday we took her to her primary care provider and they then referred her to ER for the heart racing and a EKG. The increased light headedness, feeling like she will pass out even while laying in bed, dizziness has all increased and her lymph nodes continue to be swollen and painful. It has been over a week since the vaccine and there is no clear sign of her reaction getting any better, if not worse. The EKG results indicated a new abnormality and we are trying to get her to a cardiologist. She is and had been a very healthy, varsity athlete that runs over 30 hours a week with track, and since receiving the first dose of the Moderna vaccine is unable to move very far within the house without feeling that she is going to pass out or that her heart rate is shooting up uncontrollably.

Cannot even walk around normally; swollen lymph nodes; patient cannot walk with out dizziness; Dizziness with room spinning; Unstable blood pressure; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of DIZZINESS POSTURAL (patient cannot walk with out dizziness) in an 18-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 036A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No medical history reported.). On 09-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 09-Feb-2021, the patient experienced DIZZINESS POSTURAL (patient cannot walk with out dizziness) (seriousness criterion disability), DIZZINESS (Dizziness with room spinning) and BLOOD PRESSURE FLUCTUATION (Unstable blood pressure). On 13-Feb-2021, the patient experienced LYMPHADENOPATHY (swollen lymph nodes). On an unknown date, the patient experienced GAIT INABILITY (Cannot even walk around normally). At the time of the report, DIZZINESS POSTURAL (patient cannot walk with out dizziness), DIZZINESS (Dizziness with room spinning), BLOOD PRESSURE FLUCTUATION (Unstable blood pressure), GAIT INABILITY (Cannot even walk around normally) and LYMPHADENOPATHY (swollen lymph nodes) had not resolved. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 09-Feb-2021, Heart rate: increased (High) increased. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Unknown) was unknown. Relevant Text: The Patient's mother reported that the patient received their first dose on 9 Feb 2021 and approximately 10 minutes post receiving the vaccine the patient developed severe dizziness and had an increase in their heart rate. The patient also had an unstable blood pressure. Few days later, the patient developed swelling in their lymph nodes. The reporter reported that the symptoms were still ongoing and now the patient cannot even walk without dizziness. It was also reported that the patient cannot even get back to the competitive sports and was not able to walk around anymore normally. The patient had multiple visits to the cardiologist, ENT, and pediatrician with no clear explanation of what happened to the patient. No Concomitant product use was reported. No treatment information was provided. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Looking at the clinical scenario, the event postural dizziness is persisting 6wks from onset with no clear explanation, it is assessed as a SAE (disability). However, medical history and concomitant medications, reports of tests/diagnostics are needed for further assessment. Additional information is requested.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. On 19-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 28-Apr-2021, the patient experienced IMMUNE THROMBOCYTOPENIA (idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura/Hematoma on thigh that was softball size/rash everywhere on body) (seriousness criteria hospitalization, medically significant and life threatening). At the time of the report, IMMUNE THROMBOCYTOPENIA (idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura/Hematoma on thigh that was softball size/rash everywhere on body) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 28-Apr-2021, Platelet count: 3 (Inconclusive) diagnosed with idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP). On 30-Apr-2021, Platelet count: 0 (Inconclusive) 0. On an unknown date, HIV test negative: (Negative) Negative/Condition was ruled out. On an unknown date, Hepatitis viral test: (Negative) Negative/Condition was ruled out. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. Patient experienced a rash on 28 Apr 2021 everywhere on her body that kept getting worse. She also had a hematoma on her thigh that was softball size and she did not remember bumping it. She went to the emergency room at Hospital at about 5 PM. They did bloodwork and her platelet count was 3 she was diagnosed with ITP idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura. She was perfectly healthy before this. This condition leads to bleeding and bruising her rash was actually very small bruises. That hospital felt she needed to be seen by a hematologist and oncologist so they transferred her to their main campus. Where she was admitted around midnight to the Hospital. They ruled out HIV and Hepatitis. They started her on a five day prednisone taper and did a 10% Privigen IV IG transfusion to try to increase her platelet count. In morning 30 Apr 2021, her platelet count was down to zero. Now they are going to do a brain magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and a platelet transfusion. 21 2021-02-04 chest discomfort About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injecti... Read more
Close
About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injection. It was sore red and beginning to swell. After a couple more hours it was difficult to even move my arm; it felt as if my tricep was almost entirely immobilized. These symptoms persisted for about three days, with increasingly less intensity, and after the fourth day, I had no adverse symptoms. Exactly six days after receiving the vaccine, the area where the injection was given (tricep) began to feel itchy. When I tried to scratch it, the itch was not relieved but only worsened and began to swell and turn red. By the following day (7 days after injection), the site of injection and area surrounding the site of injection (about 6 inches along my upper and 3-4 inches in width) had swelled up more and was significantly more inflamed than my opposite arm which hadn't changed at all. It had a similar swelling, itch, and pain to the sensation one experiences after getting bitten by a mosquito, but in this case a very very large mosquito bite. By the evening of the seventh day, I began feeling very fatigued both mentally and physically and felt very subtle body aches that usually signal the early signs of a fever (at least for me). Upon feeling feverish symptoms I made a drink of turmeric and ginger root powder with honey and laid down for about an hour in an attempt to rest. After an hour, the body aches and fatigue lessened in intensity but my arm was still swelling and now feeling hot in temperature. The itching was unbearable. I went to go take a warm shower later that night and started to feel a mixture of pressure and pain traveling up my arm and into my chest. I began feeling my lymph nodes on the left side of my breast to find that a lymph node in my armpit and another one on the side of my breast had enlarged to about two inches in diameter. They were painful to the touch and noticeably sore when left untouched. These symptoms persisted with no change for about 2 days. After two days, the swelling and itching in my arm went away but my lymph nodes were still inflamed. They did not reduce in size or in pain until about 7 days after the first signs of these symptoms. After a week all symptoms went away.

Rapid eye movement like "having a mini-seizure"; Fainted; Feeling warm; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a pharmacist concerning a 21-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and fainted and experienced to have rapid eye movement like "having a mini-seizure" and feeling of warmth. The patient's medical history included historical seizures. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 02 Feb 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number:026L20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 02 Feb 2021, a few minutes after the injection, the patient fainted then recovered but again fainted and was noted to have rapid eye movement like "having a mini-seizure". HCP managed her with ice pack as patient complained of feeling warm and she recovered in less than 30 minutes. Treatment information was not provided. The outcome for events fainted, rapid eye movement like "having a mini-seizure"" and feeling warm were resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This spontaneous report concerns a 21-year-old, female patient with historical seizures. who received experienced the patient fainted then recovered but again fainted and was noted to have rapid eye movement like "having a mini-seizure." The event occurred a few minutes after the administration of mRNA-1273 vaccine (Batch number: 026L20A, expiration date: unknown). Treatment administered include Icepack and outcome is resolved. Based on the information provided which includes a strong temporal onset between the vaccine administration and the event, a causal association cannot be excluded. However, event is confounded by the subject's history of seizures. Feeling warm is consistent with the safety profile of the product.

I think it was at this time that he had someone check her pulse. I don't know what the pulse reading was. I held her by the shoulders to keep her from falling while the doctor also steadied her and asked a worker in the room for an epi-pen. The worker didn't seem to react much to the request so he told her louder that he needed an epi-pen. She started searching her area and the doctor started yelling across the room to others that he needed an epi-pen. It seemed like others initially took the demand less urgently than they should, but eventually someone came with an epi-pen. By this time I don't think patient was very conscious, if at all. Sometime during this time the doctor also instructed someone to call 911. The doctor tried using the epi-pen but at first he had some kind of cap on it that prevented it from working. He removed the cap and not finding an easy way to have a sterilized injection site he injected the epi-pen through patient's jeans. Soon afterwards a cot was brought out and workers had me step aside as they took patient and put her on the cot. Patient seemed to gradually become more aware of her surroundings and it wasn't long before she appeared to me to be fully conscious once again. They checked her blood pressure and pulse and maybe did other tests during this time. Eventually the ambulance arrived and patient was very clear with everyone that she did not want to incur the expenses of riding in the ambulance and I offered to bring her wherever they suggested that she should go. They watched and evaluated her for a while and eventually had her sign the form declining the ambulance transportation. They suggested that she make an appointment with her doctor but did not suggest that we take patient to an emergency room. We departed and patient did not afterward seem to experience any symptoms from the vaccine other than some of the general feelings of being sick, soreness at the injection site, etc. that others report with the Moderna vaccine.

I developed Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (low levels of platelets) and menorrhagia due to the vaccine according to my doctor. I believe there have been about 30 cases of this occurring so far. In my case, I took the vaccine and felt relatively tired for two days. There were no other symptoms. About a week later, I got my period after not having it for a couple months. The blooding was light for a few days, but then got extremely heavy. After about a week of very heavy bleeding, I went to urgent care. They took blood tests, and found that I had a critically low level of platelets (6 platelets when the normal range is 150-400). I was admitted to the ER for multiple days, and they gave a platelet transfusion and IVIG fluids, which has helped considerably. I also had to take steroids to suppress my immune system so that my platelets could increase.

Fainting; Dizziness; Body ache; Joint pain; A spontaneous report was received from a 22-year-old female consumer, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine and experienced dizziness, fainting, joint pain, and body aches. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 31 Dec 2020 at 13:30, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 31 Dec 2020, after vaccine administration, the patient experienced dizziness, fainting, joint pain, and body aches. No treatment information was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome for the events, dizziness, fainting, joint pain, and body aches, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 22 year-old, female patient, who experienced events of dizziness, fainting, joint pain, and body aches. The events occurred on the same day after the first dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the events are assessed as possibly related.

Close
Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels like she has the hiccups where she can barely get the words to talk; when she has a hiccup her whole chest hurts; Hiccup; Numbness; Her whole right side would jerk uncontrollably; Weak; fever; itching; sore arm / burning; chills; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a consumer who was also a 22-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine who experienced sore arm/ burning (injection site pain), fever (pyrexia), chills, itching (injection site pruritus), numbness (injection site numbness), weak (asthenia), whole right side would jerk uncontrollably (myoclonus), everything went blank (loss of consciousness), couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups (aphasia), her whole chest hurt (chest discomfort), and quickly became aggravated (anger). The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in her right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a sore arm, fever, chills, itching and burning. On 07 Jan 2021, on the site where the patient received the injection, she felt numbness and weak. Her whole right-side body would jerk uncontrollably. The patient went to two emergency rooms where they stated they did not know what was wrong and gave her a steroid injection that temporarily helped calm her down. On 08 Jan 2021, the patient stared at the door and everything went blank. She could not talk and when she tried to talk, she felt like she had the hiccups. She experienced her whole chest hurting when she had a hiccup. On 25 Jan 2021 and 26 Jan 2021, the patient saw two neurologists, who did testing. The patient's jerking was random, there were no triggers for it, and she did not know how to control or stop it. These adverse reactions made the patient become aggravated very quickly, which was not like her. On an unknown date, the patient stated it was the first day in the past month she had been able to talk all day. Treatment for the events included a steroid shot. Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome for the events, sore arm/ burning, fever, chills, itching, numbness, weak, whole right side would jerk uncontrollably, everything went blank, couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups and her whole chest hurt, and quickly became aggravated, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information which indicates a strong temporal association between the use of the product and the onset of the reported events a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Chills, fever, injection site pruritus and injection site pain are consistent with the known safety profile of mRNA-1273.

22 2021-02-25 loss of consciousness Severe anaphylaxis allergic reaction; Passed out on the ground; A spontaneous report was received fr... Read more
Close
Severe anaphylaxis allergic reaction; Passed out on the ground; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 22-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and passed out on the ground and had a severe anaphylaxis allergic reaction. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On an unknown date, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. About 10 minutes after receiving the second dose of the Moderna vaccine, the patient passed out on the ground having a severe anaphylaxis allergic reaction. Treatment for the event included two doses of epinephrine IM in addition to diphenhydramine, ondansetron, and steroids to prevent a rebound reaction. 911 was called and after epinephrine and diphenhydramine were administered, the patient was immediately transported to the hospital where she stayed for 6 more hours for observation, fluids, and further medications. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable. The events, passed out on the ground and severe anaphylaxis allergic reaction, were considered resolved; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Anaphylactic reaction is a listed event in CCDS.

The vaccine was administered to the patient in the consultation room. Once we left the consultation room, after about 2 minutes, the patient got my attention and complained of feeling dizzy. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of the event, syncope, was unknown. The events, weakness and twitching of the face, were considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 23-year-old, female, who experienced serious unexpected event of syncope, and non-serious unexpected events of asthenia and muscle twitching. The events of syncope, asthenia occurred 2 days after mRNA-1273 (Lot# 025J20-2A), while the event of muscle twitching occurred on an unspecified date after mRNA-1273 (Lot# 025J20-2A). Treatment details were not provided. Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. No treatment information was provided. The Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome for the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 24 year old female patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of loss of consciousness and non-serious expected event of injection site pain and headache. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Close
Initial reaction was severe nausea and within hours developed into excruciating headache, coordination issues and depth perception loss. As patient is employee, she first contacted Health multiple times in the days immediately following the vaccine and no major concern. As symptoms continued over the weekend, she was take to an urgent care on Monday and referred to neurologist, Dr. Patient (who has emergency room scribe work experience) expressed to all 3 providers that she was concerned about stroke but was told she was too young & healthy and it was likely inflammation due to a vaccine reaction. Dr scheduled her for a brain MRI one week later, on Jan.19th (2 weeks after vaccine). Bilateral occipital brain hemorrahges. was immediately seen on the MRI and patient was rushed to emergency and then admitted for very thorough testing and scanning over the course of 5 days, including cerebral angiogram and lumbar puncture. No abnormal vascular nor blood issues were found, nor clots. Patient discharged on 1/23 w/severe headache thought to be due to lumbar puncture, continued feeling very poorly for next 2 days at home then collapsed on 1/25 and readmitted with new, massive brain bleed and multiple clots detected. I'm running out of time so you'll have to read the reports but the conclusion now is hemorrhages due to the vaccine.

25 2021-05-10 loss of consciousness, fainting Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy... Read more
Close
Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy. The patient was sitting at the time. A law enforcement officer witnessed her becoming faint and ran over to attend her. I was called over to assess her as well. The law enforcement officer called EMS. The patient stated that she felt faint, dizzy, she said she had a headache, blurry vision, and was nauseous. The patient appeared sweaty and she appeared to loose consciousness briefly twice. She did not show any signs of redness, rash, or swelling. After sitting for a few minutes, and before EMS arrived, the patient said she was improving. She did not lose consciousness anymore but she still had a headache, nausea, and blurry vision. When EMS arrived they recommended that she get checked out at the emergency room, but the patient refused stating that she did not want to go to the hospital and that she was feeling better. The patient called her parents and they came and picked her up.
